00:16:24,577 --> 00:16:25,655
like Tou Tou.

280
00:16:25,738 --> 00:16:26,815
My son's affairs

281
00:16:26,898 --> 00:16:27,898
are my affairs.

282
00:16:28,457 --> 00:16:29,588
I have to take care of it.

283
00:16:30,524 --> 00:16:31,524
Did you hear me?

284
00:16:32,257 --> 00:16:33,997
Ask Meng Meng to leave tomorrow morning.

285
00:16:35,538 --> 00:16:36,538
Mr Ren?

286
00:16:44,457 --> 00:16:45,457
I can't sleep now.

287
00:17:20,658 --> 00:17:22,257
Wake up in the morning,

288
00:17:22,418 --> 00:17:23,977
embrace the sun.

289
00:17:24,097 --> 00:17:25,458
Let your body be filled with

290
00:17:25,737 --> 00:17:26,575
radiant sunlight.

291
00:17:26,658 --> 00:17:28,458
Change your ringtone now.

292
00:17:32,898 --> 00:17:34,977
Why are you acting up
early in the morning?

293
00:17:36,337 --> 00:17:39,207
Did you know that your ringtone
gave Meng Meng a fright last night?

294
00:17:42,137 --> 00:17:43,137
I mean,

295
00:17:43,418 --> 00:17:44,575
I'm using

296
00:17:44,658 --> 00:17:45,857
the trending ringtone,

297
00:17:46,257 --> 00:17:47,737
you know, The Standing Groundhog.

298
00:17:48,578 --> 00:17:49,578
Stop it.

299
00:17:50,617 --> 00:17:51,658
That's how it screamed.

300
00:17:52,337 --> 00:17:53,414
What's so scary about it?

301
00:17:53,497 --> 00:17:56,617
Do you know how the screaming
groundhog is eaten by the predators?

302
00:17:57,898 --> 00:17:58,898
I don't want to know.

303
00:17:59,097 --> 00:18:00,097
Change it now.

304
00:18:00,377 --> 00:18:01,477
I got it.

305
00:18:01,560 --> 00:18:02,774
When Meng Meng wakes up later,

306
00:18:02,857 --> 00:18:05,338
I'll let her choose a ringtone
she likes, okay?

307
00:18:05,480 --> 00:18:06,480
Like that one...

308
00:18:14,737 --> 00:18:16,257
What are you singing?

309
00:18:16,617 --> 00:18:17,617
Where is Meng Meng?

310
00:18:17,977 --> 00:18:18,934
She's still sleeping.

311
00:18:19,017 --> 00:18:20,975
Dad, Meng Meng slept late last night.

312
00:18:21,058 --> 00:18:22,294
Let her sleep a little longer.

313
00:18:22,377 --> 00:18:23,277
Wake her up.

314
00:18:23,360 --> 00:18:26,174
A regular daily routine is necessary
for the body to function properly.

315
00:18:26,257 --> 00:18:27,257
Go and wake her up.

316
00:18:29,257 --> 00:18:30,037
Hang on,

317
00:18:30,120 --> 00:18:32,134
she was frightened last night.
Why didn't I hear...

318
00:18:32,217 --> 00:18:33,217
Master.

319
00:18:34,658 --> 00:18:35,658
Let's have breakfast.

320
00:18:38,017 --> 00:18:39,137
It's barbecued pork bun!

321
00:18:39,377 --> 00:18:41,030
We're having barbecued pork bun today.

322
00:18:44,257 --> 00:18:45,778
-What's wrong?
-Sit down and wait.

323
00:18:46,510 --> 00:18:47,709
What I am waiting for?

324
00:18:47,840 --> 00:18:49,147
Wait until everyone's here.

325
00:18:49,230 --> 00:18:50,230
Wait for your elders.

326
00:18:53,240 --> 00:18:54,240
Senior Brother!

327
00:18:55,560 --> 00:18:56,534
Senior Brother, please.

328
00:18:56,617 --> 00:18:58,134
Master, take your seat now.

329
00:18:58,217 --> 00:18:59,778
-Grandma.
-What are you doing?

330
00:19:00,444 --> 00:19:01,444
Come.

331
00:19:02,497 --> 00:19:03,497
The elders are here.

332
00:19:03,584 --> 00:19:04,584
Can I dig in now?

333
00:19:05,800 --> 00:19:06,800
What now?

334
00:19:11,217 --> 00:19:12,435
What is the meaning of this?

335
00:19:16,898 --> 00:19:18,977
What... What organization is this?

336
00:19:19,578 --> 00:19:20,617
The morning pulse

337
00:19:21,257 --> 00:19:24,257
accurately reflects our body's condition.

338
00:19:24,400 --> 00:19:26,520
This is the daily mandatory lesson
in our family.

339
00:19:26,617 --> 00:19:27,654
Put your arms out.

340
00:19:27,737 --> 00:19:29,815
Can't we have breakfast first?

341
00:19:29,898 --> 00:19:31,134
Let's read the pulse
after breakfast, okay?

342
00:19:31,217 --> 00:19:32,134
I'm starving.

343
00:19:32,217 --> 00:19:33,348
It won't be accurate then.

344
00:19:34,377 --> 00:19:35,497
Tou Tou, I'll teach you.

345
00:19:35,698 --> 00:19:36,698
Front.

346
00:19:37,698 --> 00:19:38,698
Middle.

347
00:19:39,458 --> 00:19:40,458
Rear.

348
00:19:40,977 --> 00:19:41,977
Feel it.

349
00:19:46,617 --> 00:19:47,617
Front.

350
00:19:47,938 --> 00:19:48,938
Middle.

351
00:19:49,137 --> 00:19:50,137
Rear.

352
00:19:55,778 --> 00:19:56,654
Feel any changes?

353
00:19:56,737 --> 00:19:57,737
It's beating.

354
00:19:58,658 --> 00:19:59,745
Your reading is accurate.

355
00:20:00,617 --> 00:20:01,617
I remember,

356
00:20:01,898 --> 00:20:04,414
the first time Tian Zhen
read someone's pulse when he was little,

357
00:20:04,497 --> 00:20:06,698
he said the same thing,
"It's beating."

358
00:20:08,097 --> 00:20:09,458
Tou Tou is right.

359
00:20:09,778 --> 00:20:11,298
If the pulse doesn't beat,

360
00:20:11,840 --> 00:20:13,037
it means the person is dead.

361
00:20:13,120 --> 00:20:14,180
Other than it's beating,

362
00:20:14,377 --> 00:20:15,508
do you feel anything else?

363
00:20:16,257 --> 00:20:17,134
Nothing.

364
00:20:17,217 --> 00:20:18,617
What else can I feel?

365
00:20:19,257 --> 00:20:20,257
I feel hungry.

366
00:20:20,658 --> 00:20:22,157
I just want to eat barbecued pork bun.

367
00:20:22,240 --> 00:20:23,959
You are just starting to learn now.

368
00:20:24,497 --> 00:20:25,934
As time goes on,

369
00:20:26,017 --> 00:20:29,337
you will be able to feel the
differences in the beating of the pulse.

370
00:20:29,898 --> 00:20:30,898
When?

371
00:20:31,818 --> 00:20:33,538
When will I feel the difference?

372
00:20:33,720 --> 00:20:35,200
How do I know it's different?

373
00:20:35,418 --> 00:20:37,737
Everyone's pulse is unique.

374
00:20:37,977 --> 00:20:40,353
Some people may have a pulse that
is like a rapid and forceful current,

375
00:20:40,436 --> 00:20:42,868
some may have a pulse
that is like turbulent waves.

376
00:20:42,951 --> 00:20:44,160
Some may have a pulse

377
00:20:44,277 --> 00:20:46,637
that is like plucking the strings
of a musical instrument,

378
00:20:46,720 --> 00:20:49,416
and some whose pulse is quick
and sharp like flicking a marble.

379
00:20:51,436 --> 00:20:52,237
Remember,

380
00:20:52,320 --> 00:20:53,880
as you continue
to practice pulse reading,

381
00:20:53,963 --> 00:20:55,815
you will gradually
gain clarity and insight.

382
00:20:55,898 --> 00:20:56,938
This is mysticism.

383
00:20:57,117 --> 00:20:58,237
Not at all.

384
00:20:59,178 --> 00:21:00,368
After reading pulses for a long time,

385
00:21:00,451 --> 00:21:03,410
when you place your fingers
on your patients' pulse,

386
00:21:03,520 --> 00:21:05,561
you can gain insights
into their character

387
00:21:05,857 --> 00:21:07,553
and what they have been doing recently.

388
00:21:08,137 --> 00:21:10,938
Ling Ian, I can tell
what you've been up to recently.

389
00:21:12,040 --> 00:21:13,040
You've just made

390
00:21:14,017 --> 00:21:15,097
barbecued pork buns.

391
00:21:17,283 --> 00:21:18,564
Nephew, read my pulse.

392
00:21:18,898 --> 00:21:21,257
Tell my about my character
and my recent experience.

393
00:21:22,000 --> 00:21:23,477
There is one thing I know for sure.

394
00:21:23,560 --> 00:21:24,560
Last night,

395
00:21:24,818 --> 00:21:26,538
you must have had the best sleep.

396
00:21:26,818 --> 00:21:27,815
That's true.

397
00:21:27,898 --> 00:21:31,217
I slept really well last night.
I feel very energetic today.

398
00:21:32,360 --> 00:21:34,600
-Come.
-Meng Meng, you got scared last night.

399
00:21:35,017 --> 00:21:36,017
Are you okay?

400
00:21:38,680 --> 00:21:39,680
Everyone's here.

401
00:21:39,818 --> 00:21:41,177
Let's dig in. Come on.

402
00:21:41,377 --> 00:21:42,377
Senior Brother,

403
00:21:43,298 --> 00:21:44,077
please.

404
00:21:44,160 --> 00:21:47,520
In humble fare and meagre grain,
ponder the toil to sustain.

405
00:21:47,960 --> 00:21:52,601
Half a thread, half a strand,
cherish them in mind.

406
00:21:54,377 --> 00:21:56,658
This family has so many rules
before eating.

407
00:21:58,960 --> 00:22:02,186
(Longevity for oneself,
longevity for the world)

408
00:22:24,720 --> 00:22:25,815
Luo Yong Xin, the specialist

409
00:22:25,898 --> 00:22:28,141
of Hepatobiliary Department
from Wuhan People's Hospital,

410
00:22:28,224 --> 00:22:29,504
sent you here?

411
00:22:29,617 --> 00:22:30,736
(Jiang Li)
That's right.

412
00:22:32,200 --> 00:22:33,437
You have a medical insurance, right?

413
00:22:33,520 --> 00:22:34,401
Yes.

414
00:22:34,484 --> 00:22:36,675
-Are your children staying with you?
-No.

415
00:22:36,758 --> 00:22:37,758
They are abroad.

416
00:22:38,898 --> 00:22:40,257
What about relatives?

417
00:22:41,178 --> 00:22:42,178
No.

418
00:22:42,517 --> 00:22:43,517
It's just me alone.

419
00:22:44,184 --> 00:22:45,503
You're living alone?

420
00:22:46,083 --> 00:22:47,642
Are you staying with a caretaker?

421
00:22:49,283 --> 00:22:50,283
Professor Ren,

422
00:22:50,424 --> 00:22:51,903
just be honest with me.

423
00:22:52,357 --> 00:22:53,676
Someone already told me

424
00:22:53,917 --> 00:22:54,877
that

425
00:22:54,960 --> 00:22:55,960
if a TCM practitioner

426
00:22:56,178 --> 00:22:58,174
recommends you to see a Western doctor,

427
00:22:58,257 --> 00:23:00,538
it means your condition is severe.

428
00:23:00,778 --> 00:23:03,294
And if a Western doctor recommends
you to see a TCM practitioner,

429
00:23:03,377 --> 00:23:05,017
it means you are beyond help.

430
00:23:05,778 --> 00:23:07,578
I've braced myself for it.

431
00:23:13,377 --> 00:23:15,898
Looks like Luo Yong Xin
can't cure your illness.

432
00:23:19,357 --> 00:23:20,357
I knew it.

433
00:23:21,058 --> 00:23:22,257
I figured it out.

434
00:23:23,738 --> 00:23:25,017
How much time do I have left?

435
00:23:26,083 --> 00:23:27,083
Tell me.

436
00:23:32,415 --> 00:23:33,813
He can't cure you,

437
00:23:33,896 --> 00:23:35,817
but it doesn't mean I can't cure you too.

438
00:23:36,377 --> 00:23:37,377
You can cure me?

439
00:23:39,377 --> 00:23:41,014
Dr Luo is the top expert

440
00:23:41,097 --> 00:23:42,254
in the country

441
00:23:42,337 --> 00:23:44,294
when it comes to treating this condition.

442
00:23:44,377 --> 00:23:45,277
Yes.

443
00:23:45,360 --> 00:23:47,054
That's in the domain of Western medicine.

444
00:23:47,137 --> 00:23:48,977
You haven't tried TCM's treatment yet.

445
00:23:50,096 --> 00:23:51,227
What's the treatment then?

446
00:23:51,857 --> 00:23:52,761
Drinking medicine?

447
00:23:52,844 --> 00:23:53,844
Acupuncture?

448
00:23:54,256 --> 00:23:55,774
Drinking medicine and getting acupuncture

449
00:23:55,857 --> 00:23:59,017
are common treatment methods,

450
00:23:59,137 --> 00:24:01,257
but they can't cure your illness for now.

451
00:24:03,003 --> 00:24:04,243
Let me ask you,

452
00:24:04,778 --> 00:24:06,377
did you ever kill animals

453
00:24:06,977 --> 00:24:08,257
when you were young?

454
00:24:09,316 --> 00:24:11,217
No. I'm very caring and kind.

455
00:24:11,778 --> 00:24:14,857
Chickens and geese also count.

456
00:24:15,898 --> 00:24:16,815
Do

457
00:24:16,898 --> 00:24:18,295
snails and crayfish also count?

458
00:24:18,378 --> 00:24:20,018
That's even worse.

459
00:24:20,337 --> 00:24:21,737
Think about it.

460
00:24:22,017 --> 00:24:24,294
We usually eat half of a chicken

461
00:24:24,377 --> 00:24:27,294
or half a goose in a meal.

462
00:24:27,377 --> 00:24:28,818
As for crayfish

463
00:24:29,377 --> 00:24:30,414
and snails,

464
00:24:30,497 --> 00:24:31,735
we probably eat

465
00:24:31,818 --> 00:24:33,497
dozens or hundreds of them in a meal.

466
00:24:35,658 --> 00:24:36,778
In that case,

467
00:24:37,377 --> 00:24:38,934
I've really killed a lot then.

468
00:24:39,017 --> 00:24:40,204
There was a period of time

469
00:24:40,578 --> 00:24:42,297
when my spouse was in poor health.

470
00:24:42,503 --> 00:24:43,978
To treat his illness,

471
00:24:44,071 --> 00:24:45,870
I had to slaughter two pigeons every day.

472
00:24:46,337 --> 00:24:47,534
As for snails and crayfish,

473
00:24:47,617 --> 00:24:48,654
I ate a lot of them

474
00:24:48,737 --> 00:24:49,977
in a year.

475
00:24:50,337 --> 00:24:51,737
You see, you see,

476
00:24:51,898 --> 00:24:53,017
these actions

477
00:24:53,617 --> 00:24:55,661
are considered
as accumulating karmic obstacles.

478
00:24:57,857 --> 00:24:59,857
All lives are equal.

479
00:25:00,898 --> 00:25:03,617
All these grudges of life

480
00:25:03,857 --> 00:25:06,174
seem to have concentrated on you alone.

481
00:25:06,257 --> 00:25:07,538
That's why I asked

482
00:25:08,377 --> 00:25:10,695
if you are staying with your relatives.

483
00:25:10,778 --> 00:25:12,054
If you are,

484
00:25:12,137 --> 00:25:14,737
ask one of them to travel with you.

485
00:25:15,217 --> 00:25:16,977
There are so many mountains

486
00:25:17,257 --> 00:25:19,254
and rivers in our country,

487
00:25:19,337 --> 00:25:20,857
why don't you go visit them?

488
00:25:21,377 --> 00:25:23,737
You can also go to temples
and offer incense.

489
00:25:24,137 --> 00:25:25,268
That's all you need to do.

490
00:25:29,560 --> 00:25:30,560
That's it?

491
00:25:31,137 --> 00:25:31,934
No.

492
00:25:32,017 --> 00:25:33,617
I checked your blood pressure,

493
00:25:33,737 --> 00:25:35,137
and it's not very stable.

494
00:25:35,458 --> 00:25:36,763
I will prescribe some medicine

495
00:25:37,217 --> 00:25:38,737
to help stabilize your mood

496
00:25:39,857 --> 00:25:41,938
and improve your sleep.

497
00:25:45,276 --> 00:25:47,414
Just show them this prescription.

498
00:25:47,497 --> 00:25:49,137
They will collect the herbs for you.

499
00:25:50,520 --> 00:25:51,520
Come.

500
00:25:51,737 --> 00:25:52,737
Come.

501
00:25:52,891 --> 00:25:54,290
Just go to him.

502
00:25:55,818 --> 00:25:57,338
Master! Master!

503
00:25:57,497 --> 00:25:58,495
Master.

504
00:25:58,578 --> 00:25:59,578
Master, I...

505
00:25:59,857 --> 00:26:00,883
I'd like to take leave.

506
00:26:01,377 --> 00:26:02,294
Why?

507
00:26:02,377 --> 00:26:03,375
You mentioned

508
00:26:03,458 --> 00:26:05,534
about the mountains and rivers.

509
00:26:05,617 --> 00:26:07,617
I'd like to visit a temple
and pay respect too.

510
00:26:09,511 --> 00:26:11,857
I ate more crayfish
than Grandma Jiang did.

511
00:26:12,737 --> 00:26:13,737
Really.

512
00:26:13,850 --> 00:26:15,503
-About the karmic obstacles...
-Mr Ren.

513
00:26:15,977 --> 00:26:17,294
Xu Meng's medicinal herbs
have been collected.

514
00:26:17,377 --> 00:26:19,497
Would you like to decoct it here
or at home?

515
00:26:20,137 --> 00:26:22,254
There is Aconite in it.
The fire must be kept on all time.

516
00:26:22,337 --> 00:26:23,337
Got it.

517
00:26:23,497 --> 00:26:25,337
Master, I will decoct
Meng Meng's medicine.

518
00:26:27,000 --> 00:26:29,337
-I will decoct it this evening.
-How diligent.

519
00:26:31,080 --> 00:26:32,560
But you need to give me my phone.

520
00:26:33,658 --> 00:26:34,904
I need to look at the time.

521
00:26:35,097 --> 00:26:36,097
I don't want

522
00:26:36,309 --> 00:26:37,309
to overboil it.

523
00:26:39,658 --> 00:26:42,617
Fine. I will give you back your phone
when you decoct it.

524
00:26:44,636 --> 00:26:46,516
About my leave...

525
00:26:47,977 --> 00:26:49,898
You're ignoring my trouble.

526
00:26:50,857 --> 00:26:52,377
I'm a successor.

527
00:26:52,898 --> 00:26:54,538
I have a lot of karmic obstacles.

528
00:26:59,737 --> 00:27:00,737
Hello, Mum.

529
00:27:01,063 --> 00:27:02,584
(Quan, how have you been?)

530
00:27:03,497 --> 00:27:04,897
(Have you been eating well?)

531
00:27:05,047 --> 00:27:06,368
(Are you dressed warmly?)

532
00:27:06,490 --> 00:27:08,009
How's your work?

533
00:27:08,337 --> 00:27:09,857
Did your teacher compliment you?

534
00:27:10,960 --> 00:27:13,169
Don't worry about me, Mum.
I'm doing great.

535
00:27:14,097 --> 00:27:16,997
By the way, Mum, I recently checked
the weather forecast for my hometown.

536
00:27:17,080 --> 00:27:19,054
It seems that there have been
several days of heavy rain.

537
00:27:19,137 --> 00:27:20,778
How are Dad's legs?

538
00:27:21,617 --> 00:27:22,534
He's fine.

539
00:27:22,617 --> 00:27:23,720
It didn't affect our work.

540
00:27:23,803 --> 00:27:24,803
Don't worry.

541
00:27:26,517 --> 00:27:27,517
Quan,

542
00:27:27,657 --> 00:27:30,257
Dragon Boat Festival is coming soon.

543
00:27:30,857 --> 00:27:32,054
Your dad and I

544
00:27:32,137 --> 00:27:34,698
have been entrusted by the entire village

545
00:27:35,056 --> 00:27:36,934
(to bring you some delicious food.)

546
00:27:37,017 --> 00:27:38,538
Mum, you don't have to come.

547
00:27:39,137 --> 00:27:41,485
There is no need for the trouble.
I'm doing great here.

548
00:27:42,017 --> 00:27:43,174
(Don't worry.)

549
00:27:43,257 --> 00:27:44,254
The secretary

550
00:27:44,337 --> 00:27:46,217
even bought us train tickets.

551
00:27:46,497 --> 00:27:48,778
We've got to visit the city.

552
00:27:51,097 --> 00:27:52,654
You really don't have to come, Mum.

553
00:27:52,737 --> 00:27:54,375
I can take good care of myself here.

554
00:27:54,458 --> 00:27:55,458
Do you hear me?

555
00:27:57,283 --> 00:27:58,283
Hello?

556
00:28:12,217 --> 00:28:13,174
You're finally here.

557
00:28:13,257 --> 00:28:14,337
Look at the time now.

558
00:28:14,898 --> 00:28:16,942
